{"key":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01|Psa|4","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Psa","chapter":4,"textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024","parserRevision":"v11","verses":[{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Psa:4:1","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Psa","bookOrder":18,"chapter":4,"verse":1,"text":"Answer me when I call, God, who vindicates me. You freed me from affliction; be gracious to me and hear my prayer.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Psa:4:2","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Psa","bookOrder":18,"chapter":4,"verse":2,"text":"How long, exalted ones, will my honor be insulted? How long will you love what is worthless and pursue a lie? Selah","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Psa:4:3","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Psa","bookOrder":18,"chapter":4,"verse":3,"text":"Know that the Lord has set apart the faithful for himself; the Lord will hear when I call to him.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Psa:4:4","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Psa","bookOrder":18,"chapter":4,"verse":4,"text":"Be angry and do not sin; reflect in your heart while on your bed and be silent. Selah","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Psa:4:5","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Psa","bookOrder":18,"chapter":4,"verse":5,"text":"Offer sacrifices in righteousness and trust in the Lord.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Psa:4:6","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Psa","bookOrder":18,"chapter":4,"verse":6,"text":"Many are asking, “Who can show us anything good?” Let the light of your face shine on us, Lord.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:Psa:4:7","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"Psa","bookOrder":18,"chapter":4,"verse":7,"text":"You have put more joy in my heart than they have when their grain and new wine abound.","textR